initial statement:
 1169
Your Honor,

I appear before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I accept full responsibility for my actions and acknowledge the harm I have caused.

I want to provide a brief explanation of the offense and my degree of involvement. Due to a serious mistake made by my employee at work, which would have resulted in significant financial loss for my company, I allowed my anger to overpower my better judgment. In a moment of intense frustration, I pushed him to the ground and proceeded to kick him in the stomach. There is no excuse for my actions, but I want to emphasize that my intention was never to cause serious harm.

Immediately after the incident took place, I realized the gravity of my actions and the potential consequences they could have. I promptly took my employee to the nearest emergency room to ensure his well-being. I regret my actions deeply and sincerely apologize to the victim and his family for the pain and distress I have caused them.

In an attempt to make amends for my behavior, I have already taken the initiative to offer financial compensation for the victim's hospital bills. I understand that this does not undo the harm I have caused, but I hope it demonstrates my genuine remorse and willingness to make things right.

I would like to highlight that, prior to this incident, I have led a law-abiding life with no prior criminal record. While this does not excuse or diminish the severity of my actions, I believe it is important for the court to consider my lack of prior offenses as a mitigating factor.

Furthermore, I want to assure the court that I have taken this incident as a wake-up call. I am committed to making the necessary changes within myself to ensure that I do not repeat such a reckless and harmful act. I am actively seeking counseling and therapy to address the anger management issues that contributed to this incident, and I am taking steps to educate myself on how to handle stress and frustration in a healthier manner.

Finally, I want to acknowledge the suffering I have already experienced as a consequence of my actions. The guilt I carry is a heavy burden, and I am determined to use this experience to grow as an individual and become a better member of society.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I stand before you today, pleading guilty to the charge of assault. I take complete responsibility for my actions and offer my deepest apologies to the victim and his family. I am committed to making amends and to personal growth through therapy and counseling. I request your leniency and understanding as you consider my plea, taking into account my lack of prior offenses and my demonstrated willingness to take responsibility for my actions.

Thank you for your attention, Your Honor.
