NEW STATEMENT:

1007
Your Honor,

I stand before you today to plead guilty to the charge of assault. I am Aleksander Nowak, a 40-year-old individual with no criminal record. I take full responsibility for my actions and the harm that I have caused.

In regards to the incident, I acknowledge that I pushed my employee to the ground and kicked him in the stomach. I deeply regret my response, which was triggered by my extreme anger towards him due to a serious mistake he made at work. I was aware that his actions would lead to significant financial consequences for my company, and that fueled my emotions.

Immediately after the incident, I realized the gravity of my actions and took immediate measures to ensure the well-being of the victim. I promptly brought him to the nearest emergency room to receive medical attention. I felt deep remorse for the pain and distress I caused not only to the victim but also to his family. I wish to extend my sincere apologies to them once more.

To demonstrate my remorse, I have already offered to cover the remaining hospital bills for my employee. I am fully committed to meeting any reasonable requests for compensation or assistance that the victim and his family may require.

Reflecting upon this incident, I am aware of the need for personal growth and change. Therefore, I have actively sought counseling and therapy to address and manage my anger issues, which played a significant role in the assault. Additionally, I am dedicating myself to learning stress management techniques and healthier coping mechanisms for dealing with frustrations.

In conclusion, Your Honor, I appear today to plead guilty for the offense of assault. I take complete accountability for my actions and express profound regret towards the victim and his family. By actively participating in counseling and therapy, I am committed to addressing my anger management problems. Given the circumstances surrounding this incident, I humbly request your understanding and leniency.

Thank you for your consideration, Your Honor.
